\begin_layout Paragraph
Carousel- and filmstrip pattern
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another design pattern is the 
\shape italic
Carousel
\shape default
, which is a horizontal swipe- or scrollable list of items that are visually
 interesting
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Tidwell2011"

\end_inset

.
 The pattern is useful when the user does not know exactly what item he/she
 wants and thereby wants to browse between the options.
 A picture representing an item and optionally some meta data such as name,
 is usually enough representation in a Carousel.
 In 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:carousel"

\end_inset

 it is clear that the item in the middle is in focus since it is enlarged.
 By seeing the elements immediately around the focused item the user will
 get a clue about the possibility to browse.
\end_layout

