Navigation Drawer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Android Developers 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "NavigationDrawer2014"

\end_inset

 suggests that actions should be put to the right and navigation to the
 left.
 However there is a risk that putting navigational options into the action
 bar, as in (4) in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:ActionBar"

\end_inset

, may make the view cluttered due to limited space.
 To avoid this the design pattern Navigation Drawer can be used.
 The Navigation Drawer is a menu that may be dragged from the left part
 of the screen to partly cover the current view.
 It is accessed by swiping inwards from the left outside part of the screen
 or by pressing the application logo as shown in the leftmost figure in
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:navdrawerIcon"

\end_inset

.
 The menu is then used to open a desired screen as shown in the middle and
 rightmost figures in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:navdrawerIcon"

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "NavigationDrawer2014"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
